==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[πεντε]]'' (pente) and ''[[αλφα]]'' (alpha), five alphas.

===Noun===
'''pentalpha'''

# A [[pentagram]], so called for its resemblance to five alphas superimposed at different rotations.

